Section 1:
1 L.D. 1003
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 650, L.D. 1003, “An Act Establishing
10 the Retirement Benefit Improvement Fund”
11 Amend the bill in section 2 in art. 10 in §17446 in subsection 4 in the 4th line (page 2,
12 line 16 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "labor" and inserting the following:
13 'retirement matters'
14 Amend the bill by inserting after section 2 the following:
15 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
16 allocations are made.
17 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
18 Retirement Benefit Improvement Fund N521
19 Initiative: Provides base allocations to authorize the expenditure of funds to pay for
20 retirement benefit improvements for retired state employees and teachers and their
21 beneficiaries.
22 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
23 All Other $500 $500
24 __________ __________
25 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $500 $500
2262 '
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment clarifies that the Chief Executive Officer of the Maine Public
3311 Employees Retirement System must report on the status of the Retirement Benefit
3322 Improvement Fund to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
3333 over retirement matters as opposed to the joint standing committee of the Legislature
Page 1 - 132LR1598(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 650, L.D. 1003
314 having jurisdiction over labor matters. The amendment also adds an appropriations and
325 allocations section.
336 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
347 (See attached)
